1
00:00:04,404 --> 00:00:06,974
[theme music]

2
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:53,280
SAI (VOICEOVER): Hikaru
is starting on the path

3
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,649
to the Divine Move.

4
00:01:55,682 --> 00:01:58,151
It won't be me that finds it.

5
00:01:58,151 --> 00:02:00,420
It'll be Hikaru.

6
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:04,524
The destiny set by the spirits
of Go cannot be changed.

7
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:19,740
-That's weird.

8
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:22,175
Is it my imagination,
or has the stain

9
00:02:22,209 --> 00:02:24,544
started to disappear
since last time I saw it?

10
00:02:34,588 --> 00:02:36,123
SAI (VOICEOVER):
Just as I feared.

11
00:02:42,229 --> 00:02:45,298
Destiny will take its course.

12
00:02:45,332 --> 00:02:49,136
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): Hm, maybe
it's always been like that.

13
00:02:49,136 --> 00:02:51,538
It's so long ago,
I don't remember.

14
00:02:51,571 --> 00:02:53,507
-Hey, there, Hikaru.

15
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:55,475
-Yeah?

16
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:57,277
-What are you doing tomorrow?

17
00:02:57,277 --> 00:03:00,313
Your grandmother and I were
planning to go see a play.

18
00:03:00,347 --> 00:03:02,649
You interested in
coming with us?

19
00:03:02,683 --> 00:03:04,284
-A play?

20
00:03:04,317 --> 00:03:06,553
I've got this Go
seminar tomorrow night.

21
00:03:06,553 --> 00:03:09,222
They're putting me up in
a hotel and everything.

22
00:03:09,256 --> 00:03:12,292
There's going to be about
150 people taking part.

23
00:03:12,292 --> 00:03:14,995
I have to do teaching
games, stuff like that.

24
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:15,629
-What?

25
00:03:15,629 --> 00:03:16,430
You?

26
00:03:16,463 --> 00:03:17,998
-I'm not the only one.

27
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,033
There'll be a few other
pros there as well.

28
00:03:24,571 --> 00:03:26,406
-Fancy a game with your grandpa?

29
00:03:26,406 --> 00:03:27,708
If you don't have to rush off.

30
00:03:27,741 --> 00:03:29,209
-Sure.

31
00:03:29,242 --> 00:03:30,744
And tell you what, if you beat
me, I'll give you 1,000 yen.

32
00:03:30,977 --> 00:03:32,446
-Why you little rascal.

33
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:33,280
You're on.

34
00:03:35,982 --> 00:03:37,384
-Hikaru.

35
00:03:37,417 --> 00:03:38,652
-Hm?

36
00:03:38,685 --> 00:03:40,721
-I'd rather we went home so
you could have a game with me

37
00:03:40,754 --> 00:03:43,323
instead.

38
00:03:43,356 --> 00:03:45,492
You can play your
grandfather any time.

39
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:50,697
-I don't know
what's got into you.

40
00:03:50,697 --> 00:03:52,632
We play each other all the time.

41
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:54,367
I don't see grandpa
very often, so I

42
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:56,269
should take the chance
to play him when I can.

43
00:03:56,303 --> 00:03:57,671
Come on, let's go, Sai.

44
00:03:57,671 --> 00:04:01,708
-But Hikaru-- Hikaru, I-- wait.

45
00:04:05,679 --> 00:04:06,980
You don't understand.

46
00:04:07,013 --> 00:04:08,315
I'm going to be
leaving here soon.

47
00:04:17,157 --> 00:04:20,060
-Come on, aren't you ever going
to stop worrying about that?

48
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:21,328
It's ridiculous.

49
00:04:21,361 --> 00:04:25,198
You've been around for 1,000
years and everything's fine.

50
00:04:25,232 --> 00:04:27,501
You better not be trying to
make me feel sorry for you

51
00:04:27,534 --> 00:04:29,069
just so you can
get your own way.

52
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:30,437
Because that's
not going to work.

53
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:32,405
You've been acting
selfishly lately,

54
00:04:32,405 --> 00:04:34,708
and I'm getting tired of it.

55
00:04:34,741 --> 00:04:37,577
I'm going to play grandpa,
and you'll just have to watch.

56
00:04:40,547 --> 00:04:41,748
What are you waiting for?

57
00:04:41,982 --> 00:04:42,716
Come on.

58
00:04:47,387 --> 00:04:48,488
SAI (VOICEOVER): Oh, Hikaru.

59
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:53,727
He doesn't understand.

60
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:11,511
[music plays]

61
00:05:31,565 --> 00:05:32,365
-Hi.

62
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:33,366
Is this where you check in?

63
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,536
-Yes, hello, Shindo.

64
00:05:36,536 --> 00:05:38,738
Here is an updated
schedule for you.

65
00:05:38,972 --> 00:05:44,277
You're staying in room 303 along
with Mr. Nagai and Mr. Yokoi.

66
00:05:44,311 --> 00:05:46,580
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): Mr. Ogata's
going to be here to too?

67
00:05:46,613 --> 00:05:48,114
Oh, I better keep a low profile.

68
00:05:48,148 --> 00:05:50,217
I don't want him
bothering me about Sai.

69
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:57,390
-Seiji Ogata is one
of those rare pros

70
00:05:57,424 --> 00:05:58,592
who can play any style of Go.

71
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:01,161
But his opponent, Ms.
Haruki, is the kind of player

72
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:03,997
who keeps on fighting back.

73
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:05,699
Well, well, that's
an interesting move

74
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:07,541
from Ogata-sensei.

75
00:06:07,541 --> 00:06:08,361
Hm.

76
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:13,540
I have a feeling he'll regret
that move later in the game.

77
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,275
But I should be
careful what I say,

78
00:06:15,308 --> 00:06:18,445
or I'll get myself into
trouble with Mr. Ogata.

79
00:06:18,478 --> 00:06:20,380
-Ashiwara.

80
00:06:20,413 --> 00:06:22,082
-You see what I mean?

81
00:06:22,115 --> 00:06:25,018
[laughter]

82
00:06:45,266 --> 00:06:47,201
-This ending here won't
give immediate results,

83
00:06:47,235 --> 00:06:48,936
but it has another purpose.

84
00:06:48,970 --> 00:06:51,372
If you decide that you
want to push through,

85
00:06:51,406 --> 00:06:53,007
this movie is going
to help you force

86
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:54,242
your way towards that goal.

87
00:06:54,275 --> 00:06:56,077
Of course, there's
more to it than that.

88
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:58,980
-Ah, it's making sense.

89
00:06:59,013 --> 00:07:01,082
-Shindo.

90
00:07:01,115 --> 00:07:03,184
What are you doing
still playing?

91
00:07:03,184 --> 00:07:05,987
Isn't it way past your bedtime?

92
00:07:06,020 --> 00:07:08,156
-Gah, Ogata-sensei.

93
00:07:08,189 --> 00:07:09,924
-Hey, there's no reason
to be all scared.

94
00:07:09,924 --> 00:07:12,193
I just came to play a little Go.

95
00:07:12,226 --> 00:07:14,062
-Have you and him
been out tonight?

96
00:07:14,095 --> 00:07:16,931
-Yeah, I took him
out on the town.

97
00:07:16,964 --> 00:07:19,500
We had to celebrate him
winning the Judan title.

98
00:07:19,734 --> 00:07:24,205
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): Ugh, maybe
a bit too much celebrating.

99
00:07:24,238 --> 00:07:27,308
-Hey, Shindo.

100
00:07:27,308 --> 00:07:29,410
-Yeah?

101
00:07:29,444 --> 00:07:33,181
-Let me play Sai.

102
00:07:33,181 --> 00:07:36,217
-But Ogata-sensei, I already
told you I don't know Sai.

103
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:39,387
How can I let you play
him if I don't know him?

104
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:42,990
-Hikaru, I think
we should play him

105
00:07:43,024 --> 00:07:45,193
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): Sai,
you're being selfish again.

106
00:07:45,193 --> 00:07:48,196
-It's OK for me to play him
when he's in this condition.

107
00:07:48,196 --> 00:07:50,164
I'm sure he won't
know I'm his opponent.

108
00:07:50,198 --> 00:07:51,299
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): Really?

109
00:07:54,202 --> 00:07:55,470
What's the point?

110
00:07:55,503 --> 00:07:57,505
He doesn't look in good
enough shape to play.

111
00:07:57,739 --> 00:08:01,042
You wouldn't want a game with
someone when they're like that.

112
00:08:01,042 --> 00:08:03,010
SAI (VOICEOVER): I may
never have an opportunity

113
00:08:03,044 --> 00:08:05,279
to play a serious
game against him.

114
00:08:05,313 --> 00:08:07,782
-It doesn't really
matter how it turns out.

115
00:08:07,815 --> 00:08:09,951
If I can go a little
way towards fulfilling

116
00:08:09,984 --> 00:08:12,987
the demand he made to
you at the hospital--

117
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:16,090
-Let me play him.

118
00:08:16,124 --> 00:08:17,191
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): Uh huh.

119
00:08:17,225 --> 00:08:18,926
I guess it wouldn't hurt.

120
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,461
Playing you might be
a nice way for him

121
00:08:20,495 --> 00:08:21,929
to celebrate his Judan win.

122
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:27,235
-Come on, Shindo.

123
00:08:27,268 --> 00:08:28,803
Let me play Sai.

124
00:08:28,836 --> 00:08:29,971
-I've got a better idea.

125
00:08:30,004 --> 00:08:31,586
Why don't you and
me have a game?

126
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,040
-What?

127
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:34,175
Now?

128
00:08:34,208 --> 00:08:35,910
-Can you believe the kid
wants to challenge Sensei

129
00:08:35,943 --> 00:08:37,245
by playing him in
that condition?

130
00:08:45,887 --> 00:08:47,922
-Well, you're not
Sai, but I guess

131
00:08:47,955 --> 00:08:49,090
you're going to have to do.

132
00:08:52,059 --> 00:08:53,928
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): He
doesn't look too good.

133
00:08:53,961 --> 00:08:56,764
I don't know if he'll
even be able to play.

134
00:08:56,764 --> 00:08:59,433
But a game against you might
help him feel a bit better.

135
00:09:03,271 --> 00:09:05,907
What's with the long face now?

136
00:09:05,940 --> 00:09:08,476
I'm letting you
play him, aren't I?

137
00:09:08,509 --> 00:09:09,443
Hm, geez.

138
00:09:18,486 --> 00:09:20,388
I'll let you play
for Mr. Ogata's sake.

139
00:09:20,421 --> 00:09:21,889
But you've got to cheer up.

140
00:09:21,923 --> 00:09:26,327
Because it's starting to be no
fun hanging around with you.

141
00:09:26,327 --> 00:09:27,795
SAI (VOICEOVER): Why?

142
00:09:27,829 --> 00:09:30,064
Why Hikaru and not me?

143
00:09:30,097 --> 00:09:33,968
Spirits of Go, tell me!

144
00:09:34,001 --> 00:09:36,003
Why Hikaru?

145
00:09:36,037 --> 00:09:36,504
Why him?

146
00:09:40,474 --> 00:09:44,345
Soon I will be gone and
only he will remain.

147
00:09:52,353 --> 00:09:55,456
I cannot help feeling
envious of him.

148
00:09:55,456 --> 00:09:57,925
He has his whole
future ahead of him.

149
00:10:01,195 --> 00:10:02,363
But that's not all.

150
00:10:05,032 --> 00:10:08,970
I don't want to leave him.

151
00:10:09,003 --> 00:10:11,439
I didn't want to
leave Torajiro either.

152
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:26,020
The memory of him on his death
bed is still very strong.

153
00:10:32,927 --> 00:10:40,501
He said to me, "Sai, I'm sorry."

154
00:10:43,971 --> 00:10:45,206
I didn't want him to go.

155
00:10:49,877 --> 00:10:51,879
But I was given no choice.

156
00:10:58,986 --> 00:10:59,954
I'm sorry, Hikaru.

157
00:11:02,857 --> 00:11:04,225
I will have to leave you soon.

158
00:11:14,468 --> 00:11:17,438
[grunting]

159
00:11:17,471 --> 00:11:19,440
-I didn't know you were in here.

160
00:11:19,473 --> 00:11:21,075
Sorry if we woke you.

161
00:11:21,108 --> 00:11:23,077
-No, that's OK.

162
00:11:23,110 --> 00:11:24,812
Just turn out the
light, would you?

163
00:11:28,015 --> 00:11:30,017
-We should have enough
light if we play over here

164
00:11:30,051 --> 00:11:32,920
by the window.

165
00:11:32,954 --> 00:11:33,676
Sit down.

166
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,936
-You're still thirsty?

167
00:11:48,970 --> 00:11:50,371
-It's been a long and I'm tired.

168
00:11:50,404 --> 00:11:52,139
That'll be my handicap.

169
00:11:52,173 --> 00:11:55,142
I doubt I'm going to put up
much of a fight in this game.

170
00:11:55,176 --> 00:11:56,744
-Easier for me to win.

171
00:11:56,777 --> 00:12:00,314
Don't expect me to take
it easy on you, OK?

172
00:12:00,348 --> 00:12:02,917
-Hey, hey, you can't
treat it like a real game

173
00:12:02,950 --> 00:12:04,218
when I'm in this state.

174
00:12:04,251 --> 00:12:06,954
Save your tough guy act
for an official match.

175
00:12:06,954 --> 00:12:10,424
I already got an idea of
what your skill level is.

176
00:12:10,458 --> 00:12:13,361
I was there watching when you
played your Shinshodan Series

177
00:12:13,394 --> 00:12:14,395
game.

178
00:12:14,428 --> 00:12:15,997
Kuwabara-sensei and
I were taking bets

179
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:18,466
on who was going to win.

180
00:12:18,499 --> 00:12:20,368
Kuwabara got in
first and bet on you,

181
00:12:20,401 --> 00:12:22,937
which meant I was left with
no choice but to bet on Toya.

182
00:12:26,073 --> 00:12:27,375
But if you want
to know the truth,

183
00:12:27,408 --> 00:12:29,343
my money would have
been on you as well.

184
00:12:29,377 --> 00:12:30,511
-Hmph, right.

185
00:12:30,745 --> 00:12:32,480
You expect me to believe
you when you're like this?

186
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,782
-You really are a brat.

187
00:12:34,815 --> 00:12:38,152
Although I am a lot more
tired today than unusual.

188
00:12:38,185 --> 00:12:40,821
Winning the Judan Series
title is a big deal.

189
00:12:40,821 --> 00:12:44,825
So I think I deserve to go
out and celebrate a bit.

190
00:12:44,859 --> 00:12:48,162
Toya-sensei's retirement was
turned everything upside down.

191
00:12:51,065 --> 00:12:52,933
Even though I won
the Judan title,

192
00:12:52,933 --> 00:12:55,302
people won't recognize
me as a champion

193
00:12:55,336 --> 00:13:00,074
unless I can successfully
defended it next year.

194
00:13:00,074 --> 00:13:01,075
You'll see.

195
00:13:01,108 --> 00:13:02,343
I'm going to be the
best in the world.

196
00:13:10,818 --> 00:13:19,293
So, Shindo, like I said
before-- let me play Sai.

197
00:13:19,326 --> 00:13:20,761
-Settle for playing me?

198
00:13:29,070 --> 00:13:30,304
-Sure. Why not?

199
00:13:36,110 --> 00:13:37,178
16.

200
00:13:37,211 --> 00:13:39,313
You go first.

201
00:13:39,346 --> 00:13:41,449
-Onegaishimasu.

202
00:13:41,482 --> 00:13:42,049
-Yeah.

203
00:14:22,857 --> 00:14:24,859
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): Well,
it looks like I've won.

204
00:14:24,892 --> 00:14:25,960
It's all over.

205
00:14:30,231 --> 00:14:32,099
-Wait.

206
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:35,069
-You made a big mistake on
an easy life and death play.

207
00:14:35,102 --> 00:14:39,073
You must be really
out of it to do that.

208
00:14:39,073 --> 00:14:41,909
-My mistake hasn't got
anything to do with it.

209
00:14:41,942 --> 00:14:44,044
Let's face it, you played well.

210
00:14:44,078 --> 00:14:48,482
You went on the attack over
in the upper right corner.

211
00:14:48,482 --> 00:14:54,088
My keystones were useless after
that, so what was the point?

212
00:14:54,121 --> 00:14:56,157
After that, my
heart wasn't in it,

213
00:14:56,190 --> 00:14:58,159
so I played some
pretty reckless moves.

214
00:14:58,192 --> 00:15:00,961
I'm surprised it took
you that long to beat me.

215
00:15:00,961 --> 00:15:03,998
-Maybe if we'd played
earlier in the day.

216
00:15:04,031 --> 00:15:05,332
HIKARU (VOICEOVER):
Was it really

217
00:15:05,332 --> 00:15:08,836
worth letting him play Sai?

218
00:15:08,869 --> 00:15:11,972
If he actually knew who
he'd been playing against,

219
00:15:12,006 --> 00:15:14,074
I'd have been in big trouble.

220
00:15:14,074 --> 00:15:16,010
But then again, he couldn't
have figured it out

221
00:15:16,043 --> 00:15:17,478
while he's like this.

222
00:15:17,511 --> 00:15:21,215
-Well, good night, Mr. Ogata.

223
00:15:25,219 --> 00:15:29,190
HIKARU (VOICEOVER): It's kind
of sad, him losing this way.

224
00:15:29,223 --> 00:15:30,824
-Some of those moves
were masterful.

225
00:15:30,824 --> 00:15:33,093
There was no mistakes.

226
00:15:33,093 --> 00:15:37,298
It was as if I was playing Sai.

227
00:15:37,331 --> 00:15:41,135
[chuckling] But that's absurd.

228
00:15:41,168 --> 00:15:43,504
I'm just imagining things.

229
00:15:43,737 --> 00:15:45,272
HIKARU (VOICEOVER):
Hopefully that game's

230
00:15:45,306 --> 00:15:48,242
got him off my back for a while.

231
00:15:48,275 --> 00:15:50,377
I'll skip out of here
early tomorrow morning

232
00:15:50,411 --> 00:15:52,813
so I don't bump into him again.

233
00:15:52,846 --> 00:15:53,968
Sai?

234
00:16:08,436 --> 00:16:11,205
-In the actual game, white
went after black's eye space

235
00:16:11,239 --> 00:16:12,307
by playing here.

236
00:16:12,307 --> 00:16:13,708
Now what would have
happened if white

237
00:16:13,741 --> 00:16:15,777
had connected in
the center first?

238
00:16:15,810 --> 00:16:18,346
White would wait for this move,
and then go on to play an--

239
00:16:18,379 --> 00:16:21,716
-Ogata-sensei,
how are you today?

240
00:16:21,716 --> 00:16:23,685
-Have you seen Shindo?

241
00:16:23,718 --> 00:16:25,720
-He went back home
early this morning.

242
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:27,455
He'd finished all his
teaching sessions,

243
00:16:27,455 --> 00:16:29,357
so I guess he didn't see
any point in staying.

244
00:16:53,681 --> 00:16:55,583
[yawn]

245
00:16:55,617 --> 00:16:57,285
HIKARU: I don't know
why I'm so tired.

246
00:16:57,318 --> 00:16:58,686
I had a chance to
sleep on the train.

247
00:17:01,122 --> 00:17:03,091
I can barely stay awake.

248
00:17:06,227 --> 00:17:08,696
-Hikaru, I would
like to play a game.

249
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:09,497
-Now?

250
00:17:09,530 --> 00:17:10,431
I haven't got the energy.

251
00:17:10,465 --> 00:17:13,401
I'm too tired.

252
00:17:13,434 --> 00:17:16,371
I gotta get some sleep or else
I might get sick, you know.

